Six police officers who were charged with the murder of two brothers in Kianjokoma, Embu County have filed an application in court seeking to be released on bail pending hearing and determination of the case. The six, Benson Mbuthia, Consolota Kariuki, Nicholas Cheruiyot, Martin Wanyama, Lilian Cherono and James Mwanikiwer, have been in custody at since their arrest last month. In their bail application, the officers maintain that they will not interfere with witnesses or investigations into the matter. Last week they were each charged with two counts of murder before justice Daniel Ogembo. They denied the charges and were detained at Industrial Area and Lang’ata Women’s Remand prisons pending hearing of the bail application. The court directed that the hearing of the bail application be conducted on September 22. Also Read: The are accused of killing Benson Njiru and Emmanuel Mutura who had been arrested over violation of curfew order. Video Of The Day: | CHASING HOPE | KEMRI undertaking stem cell research for treatment of Leishmaniasis